Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the spectral efficiencies of links in interference-limited cellular networks, which is a topic related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of cellular networks, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the performance of a network of mobiles and base stations, which can be considered a social and information network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the spectral efficiencies of links, which is a topic related to multimedia communication. 
5. cs.COM (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of power control in cellular networks, which can be considered a topic related to computational complexity.
